# data frame management

## creating comments score variable
swift_pop_comments["comment_score"] = swift_pop_comments["comment_like_count"] + 1
menendez_scandal_comments["comment_score"] = menendez_scandal_comments["comment_like_count"] + 1
uvalde_horrific_comments["comment_score"] = uvalde_horrific_comments["comment_like_count"] + 1
ukraine_horrific_comments["comment_score"] = ukraine_horrific_comments["comment_like_count"] + 1

## creating dummy variables for positive, negative and neutral comments (score > 0.7)
swift_pop_comments["positive_dummy"] = swift_pop_comments['positive_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)
swift_pop_comments["neutral_dummy"] = swift_pop_comments['neutral_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)
swift_pop_comments["negative_dummy"] = swift_pop_comments['negative_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)

menendez_scandal_comments["positive_dummy"] = menendez_scandal_comments['positive_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)
menendez_scandal_comments["neutral_dummy"] = menendez_scandal_comments['neutral_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)
menendez_scandal_comments["negative_dummy"] = menendez_scandal_comments['negative_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)

uvalde_horrific_comments["positive_dummy"] = uvalde_horrific_comments['positive_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)
uvalde_horrific_comments["neutral_dummy"] = uvalde_horrific_comments['neutral_score'].apply(lambda score: 1 if score >0.7 else 0)

# Functions

## statistics

def summary_stats_comments(df):
    df[["day","comment_like_count","comment_score", "positive_score","neutral_score","negative_score"]].describe()
    
def summary_stats_vids(df):
    df[["day","video_view_count","video_comment_count","video_like_count","video_dislike_count"]].describe()
    
def bivariate_regression(df_Y, df_X):
    model = sm.OLS(df_Y, df_X)
    results = model.fit()
    print(results.summary())

## Comments over time graph

def comments_over_time(df, title):
    df2 = df.groupby('day_published').size().reset_index(name='num_comments')
    df2['day_published'] = pd.to_datetime(df2['day_published'])
    return (ggplot(df2, aes(x=df2.day_published, y=df2.num_comments)) +
     geom_line() +
     labs(x='Date', y='Comments', title=title))

def comment_scores_over_time(df, title):
    df2 = df.groupby('day_published')["comment_score"].sum().reset_index(name="comment_score")
    df2["comment_score"] = pd.to_numeric(df2["comment_score"])
    df2["day_published"] = pd.to_datetime(df2["day_published"], format='%Y-%m-%d')
    return (ggplot(df2, aes(x=df2["day_published"], y=df2["comment_score"])) +
     geom_line() +
     labs(x='Date', y='Comment Score', title=title))

def comments_per_video_over_time(topic_comment_df, topic_video_df, title):
    
    comment_df = topic_comment_df.groupby('day_published').sum().reset_index(name='num_comments')
    comment_df['day_published'] = pd.to_datetime(comment_df['day_published'])
    
    vid_df = topic_video_df.groupby('day_published').sum().reset_index(name='num_vids')
    vid_df['day_published'] = pd.to_datetime(vid_df['day_published'])
    
    comment_per_vid = pd.merge(comment_df, vid_df, on='day_published', how='inner')
    comment_per_vid["comments_per_vid"] = (comment_per_vid["num_comments"] / comment_per_vid["num_vids"])
    
    return (ggplot(comment_per_vid, aes(x=comment_per_vid.day_published, y=comment_per_vid.comments_per_vid)) +
     geom_line() +
     labs(x='Date', y='Comments per Video', title=title))


## Videos over time graph
    
def videos_over_time(df, title):
    df2 = df.groupby('day_published').size().reset_index(name='num_videos')
    df2['day_published'] = pd.to_datetime(df2['day_published'])
    return (ggplot(df2, aes(x=df2.day_published, y=df2.num_videos)) +
     geom_line() +
     labs(x='Date', y='Videos', title=title))


## data management

def merge_comments_and_videodata(topic_comment_df, topic_video_df):
    
    comment_df = topic_comment_df.groupby('day_published').size().reset_index(name='num_comments')
    comment_df['day_published'] = pd.to_datetime(comment_df['day_published'])
    
    vid_df = topic_video_df.groupby('day_published').size().reset_index(name='num_videos')
    vid_df['day_published'] = pd.to_datetime(vid_df['day_published'])
    
    comment_and_vid = pd.merge(comment_df, vid_df, on='day_published', how='inner')
    return comment_and_vid
